The inventor of the World Wide Web plans to launch a new Internet to download Google and Facebook
Tim Berners-Lee, the inventor of the World Wide Web, is launching a new company that aims to become a competitor to Facebook, Amazon and Google.
The latest project of this legendary technology, Inrupt, is a company that is developing on the basis of Berners-Lee’s open platform Solid.
Solid allows users to choose the location of their data and the people who will be allowed access to certain information.
In an exclusive interview with Fast Company, Berners-Lee joked that the intent behind Inrupt was "world domination".
“We have to do it now,” he said, referring to the startup.
“This is a historic moment.”
The app uses Solid's technology to allow people to create their own "personal network data storage" or POD.
It may contain contact lists, duty lists, calendar, music library and other personal and professional tools.
It's like Google Drive, Microsoft Outlook, Slack and Spotify are all available on one browser at a time.
What is unique when it comes to personal online data storage is that the decision on who can access which information is fully user-generated.
The company calls this “personal empowerment through data.”
The idea behind Inrupt, according to company CEO John Bruce, is to provide the company with the resources, processes and appropriate skills to help make Solid accessible to everyone.
The company currently consists of Berners-Lee, Bruce, a security platform purchased by IBM, several engineers who signed a contract to work on the project, and a community of volunteer developers.
Starting this week, developers from around the world were able to create their own decentralized applications using the tools available on the Inrupt website.
Berners-Lee said he and his team are not talking to Facebook and Google about whether or not to introduce a complete change in which all of their business models would completely reverse overnight.
“We’re not asking for their permission.”
Berners-Lee said Inrupt's "mission is to provide commercial energy and ecosystem to protect the integrity and quality of the new network built on Solid."
